<p>The <code>record</code> tag retrieves a single row from the database.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}record "columns from table where condition"{close}
  {open}$column1{close} - {open}$column2{close}
{open}/record{close}</pre>

<h2>Example: User Profile</h2>
<pre>{open}record "* from users where id = 1"{close}
  &lt;h2&gt;{open}$name{close}&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Email: {open}$email{close}&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Role: {open}$role{close}&lt;/p&gt;
{open}else{close}
  &lt;p&gt;User not found&lt;/p&gt;
{open}/record{close}</pre>

<h2>PHP Variable Method</h2>
<pre>// In PHP:
$user = db("record * from users where id = 1");

// In template:
{open}user{close}
  Name: {open}$name{close}
{open}else{close}
  Not found
{open}/user{close}</pre>

<h2>Record vs Array</h2>
<table border="1" cellpadding="5">
  <tr><th>Tag</th><th>Returns</th><th>Use Case</th></tr>
  <tr><td>{open}record{close}</td><td>First row only</td><td>Single item lookup</td></tr>
  <tr><td>{open}array{close}</td><td>All matching rows</td><td>Lists, tables</td></tr>
</table>
